          <mxGeometry x="550" y="240" width="490" height="135" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mriFYcUJs7z9-BHMGoYr-33" value="&lt;div style=&quot;background-color:#1e1f22;color:#bcbec4&quot;&gt;&lt;pre style=&quot;font-family:&#39;JetBrains Mono&#39;,monospace;font-size:9.8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#cf8e6d;&quot;&gt;public class &lt;/span&gt;LinkedList&amp;lt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#16baac;&quot;&gt;E&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;br&gt;    &lt;span style=&quot;color:#cf8e6d;&quot;&gt;extends &lt;/span&gt;AbstractSequentialList&amp;lt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#16baac;&quot;&gt;E&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;br&gt;    &lt;span style=&quot;color:#cf8e6d;&quot;&gt;implements &lt;/span&gt;List&amp;lt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#16baac;&quot;&gt;E&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;, Deque&amp;lt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#16baac;&quot;&gt;E&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;, Cloneable, java.io.Serializable&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="765" y="265" width="60" height="30" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mriFYcUJs7z9-BHMGoYr-36" value="LInkedList use Doubly linked list as underline datastructure.&lt;div&gt;Each element is stored in separate node.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="53.75" y="10" width="416.25" height="40" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mriFYcUJs7z9-BHMGoYr-37" value="&lt;b&gt;Internal structure:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;private static class Node&amp;lt;E&amp;gt; {&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; E item;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Node&amp;lt;E&amp;gt; next;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Node&amp;lt;E&amp;gt; prev;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;}&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Each node contains:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;1. Data&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;2.Address of previous node&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;3.Address of next node&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="53.75" y="50" width="206.25" height="160" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mriFYcUJs7z9-BHMGoYr-38" value="Whenever we write&amp;nbsp;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;LinkedList&amp;lt;String&amp;gt; lisst = new LinkedList&amp;lt;&amp;gt;()&lt;/b&gt;;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Internally first = null;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; last = null;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; size =0;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;No node exists&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="57.5" y="220" width="292.5" height="100" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mriFYcUJs7z9-BHMGoYr-39" value="When we add elements&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;list.add(&quot;A&quot;);&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Node created : NULL &amp;lt;- A -&amp;gt; NULL&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Add more elements&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;list.add(&quot;B&quot;);&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;list.add(&quot;C&quot;);&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Structure becomes : NULL &amp;lt;- A &amp;lt;-&amp;gt; B &amp;lt;-&amp;gt; C -&amp;gt; NULL&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Node A&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Data=A&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Prev=NULL&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Next=Node B&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Node B&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Data=B&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Prev=Node A&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Next=Node C&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Node C&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Data=C&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Prev=Node B&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Next=NULL&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="60" y="330" width="442.5" height="340" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mriFYcUJs7z9-BHMGoYr-40" value="" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="550" y="130" width="260" height="90" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mriFYcUJs7z9-BHMGoYr-41" value="Constructors :&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;LinkedList l = new LinkedList();&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;LinkedList l = new LinkedList(Collection c);&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="558.5" y="140" width="250" height="70" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mriFYcUJs7z9-BHMGoYr-42" value="" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="558.5" y="400" width="461.5" height="110" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mriFYcUJs7z9-BHMGoYr-43" value="How getIndex() works ?&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;list.get(2);&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;LInkedList cannot jump directly it traverse from node to node then returns C&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Time complexity - o(n)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;But for adding it add last so time complexity becomes&amp;nbsp; - o(1)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="568.5" y="420" width="411.5" height="70" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mriFYcUJs7z9-BHMGoYr-44" value="It is use for adding or deleting operation not best for retrieval operation. Does not implement RandomAccess" style="text;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="558.5" y="315" width="431.5" height="30" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-1" value="" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2010" y="-660" width="980" height="1640" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-2" value="" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2020" y="-645" width="60" height="20" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-3" value="HashMap" style="text;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2020" y="-642.5" width="60" height="15" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-4" value="HashMap iis a combination of Array, LinkedList, Red black Tree (Java 8+).&lt;div&gt;Internally it is actually Bucket + Nodes +Tree Nodes&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2020" y="-625" width="450" height="50" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-5" value="" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2510" y="-620" width="400" height="132.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-6" value="&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Capacity = 16&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Load factor = 0.75&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;HashMap internally uses array of buckets (Node[])&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Insertion order is not preserved based on hashcode of keys&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Duplicate keys are not allowed but values can be duplicate&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Heterogeneous/Homogeneous object are allowed&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Null is allowed for key only once, Values can have multiple null.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2500" y="-610" width="400" height="100" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-7" value="Whenever we create a HashMap :&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;HashMap&amp;lt;Integer, String&amp;gt; map = new HashMap();&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;internally its capacity =16 anf load factor = 0.75&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Bucket array :&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;0&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;1&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;2&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;3&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;4&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;5&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;6&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;7&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;8&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;9&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;10&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;11&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;12&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;13&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;14&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;15&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2030" y="-570" width="380" height="290" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-8" value="Think of it as a 16 locker. All empty" style="text;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2090" y="-342.5" width="200" height="45" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-9" value="Now if we add a element :&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;map.put(101, &quot;John&quot;);&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Hashmap decides which bucket?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Hash calculation is done i.e. key.hashcode(). For Integer 101.hashcode();&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;It returns 101.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Now HashMap calcualte the bucket here.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;HashMap uses (n-1) &amp;amp; hash&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;where n = 16 So (16-1) &amp;amp; hash = 15 &amp;amp; 101&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Convert to binary : 15 -&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; 00001111&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;101 - 01100110&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;----------------&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;AND&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;00000100&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Result : 5&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Store in bucket 5.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Secont put &lt;b&gt;map.put(102, &quot;Mike&quot;);&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;H&lt;/b&gt;ash calculated . Suppose bucket =6&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Stored :&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;5 --&amp;gt; (101, &quot;John&quot;)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;6 --&amp;gt; (102, &quot;Mike&quot;)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;get() internal working :&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Now if we &lt;b&gt;map.get(101, &quot;John&quot;);&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;It calculate hash that is 101.hashcode() returns 101. Then calculate bucket which returns 5. Go directly to bucket 5 --&amp;gt; (101, &quot;John&quot;)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Check key by equals() method. Match found return John.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;TIme complexity 0(1)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;u&gt;Why hashcode() is needed?&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Suppose there are 100 million records than without hashcode linear search hashcode helps hashmap to directly jump to data&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2030" y="-260" width="410" height="460" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-10" value="&lt;u&gt;Collision :&lt;/u&gt;&lt;div&gt;Two keys can produce the same bucket for example,&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;map.put(&quot;FB&quot;, &quot;A&quot;);&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;map.put(&quot;Ea&quot;, &quot;B&quot;);&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;produces same hashcode&amp;nbsp; 2236.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Same bucket. This is called collision&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Suppose both reach bucket 10. then Linked List created (till Java 7)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;10 --&amp;gt; FB &amp;lt;-&amp;gt; Ea&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Now how get() works in collision?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Suppose we map.get(&quot;Ea&quot;);&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Hashmap go to bucket 10.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Check FB.equals(&quot;Ea&quot;);&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; return false&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Check Ea.equals(&quot;Ea&quot;);&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; return true&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Return value&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Time complexity in bucket is 0(n)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;u&gt;Treeification :&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Till Java 7 suppose there are 1000 nodes in a bucket then time complexity is 0(n). Bad performance.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Java 8 solution :&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;When bucket size becomes more than 8 i.e bucket size &amp;gt; 8 and table size more than or equal to 64 i.e table size &amp;gt;= 64 linkedlist converts to Red Black Tree. This process is called Treefication. Before search complexity 0(n) after 0(log n)&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2030" y="200" width="370" height="390" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-11" value="&lt;u&gt;How duplicate keys work?&lt;/u&gt;&lt;div&gt;Suppose &lt;b&gt;map.put(101, &quot;John&quot;);&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;map.put(101, &quot;Mike&quot;);&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Will two entries cretaed? -&amp;gt; No&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Steps : Find bucket&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Find existing key&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Check equals()&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; returns true&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Update value that is 101 -&amp;gt; Mike . John overwritten&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2030" y="580" width="340" height="140" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-12" value="&lt;u&gt;equals() vs hashcode() :&lt;/u&gt;&lt;div&gt;HashMap uses both&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;hashcode() -&amp;gt; Use to find bucket&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;equals() - &amp;gt; Use to identify exact key in bucket&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2030" y="720" width="400" height="80" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-13" value="&lt;u&gt;Rehashing :&lt;/u&gt;&lt;div&gt;Now capacity of HashMap is 16 and load factor is 0.75&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Threshold is 16 X 0.75 = 12&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;When 13 entry comes resize. After resize capacity is 32 (16+12)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;New bucket array is created. All entries recalculated. Moved again. This process is called Rehashing.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Rehashing is very expensive so how to avoid it&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Hashamap h = new HashMap(1000);&lt;/b&gt; Provide initial capacity.&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2030" y="800" width="410" height="130" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-17" value="" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2510" y="-467.5" width="360" height="107.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-18" value="Constructors :&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;HashMap m&amp;nbsp; = new HashMap&amp;nbsp;();&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;HashMap&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;l = new HashMap&amp;nbsp;(int initialCapacity);&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;HashMap&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;l = new HashMap&amp;nbsp;(int initialCapacity, float fillRatio);&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;HashMap&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;l = new HashMap&amp;nbsp;(Map m);&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2521.25" y="-448.75" width="337.5" height="70" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-21" value="" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2480" y="720" width="490" height="180" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-22" value="&lt;h3 data-end=&quot;7509&quot; data-start=&quot;7444&quot; data-section-id=&quot;criq2f&quot;&gt;What happens if hashCode differs but equals returns true?&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div&gt;This violates the contract and causes unpredictable behavior.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Contract of hashcode and equals :&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If obj.equals(obj1), then obj.hashcode() == obj1.hashcode() should be true&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If obj.hashcode() == obj1.hashcode() is true the does not guaratee obh.equals(obj1);&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;equal() is not called when inserting first element because bucket are empty. equals() only come to picture when bucket contains the data&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p data-end=&quot;7572&quot; data-start=&quot;7511&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2500" y="750" width="460" height="120" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-23" value="" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2015" y="1050" width="985" height="790" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-26" value="" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2030" y="1065" width="70" height="20" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-27" value="Hashtable" style="text;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2030" y="1067.5" width="70" height="15" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-28" value="" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2521.25" y="-342.5" width="348.75" height="152.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-29" value="&lt;u&gt;Is HashMap backed by Hashtable?&lt;/u&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;No. HashMap and Hashtable are separate classes. However, HashMap is an implementation of the hash table data structure concept. Internally it uses an array of buckets (&lt;code data-end=&quot;2275&quot; data-start=&quot;2267&quot;&gt;Node[]&lt;/code&gt;).&amp;nbsp; Each bucket stores entries as Nodes. In case of collisions, entries are stored as a linked list, and in Java 8+, if collisions exceed a threshold, the linked list is converted into a Red-Black Tree for faster lookup&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2525.63" y="-334.37" width="340" height="136.25" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-30" value="The internal working of HashMap and Hashtable is almost same.&lt;div&gt;Suppose we create a Hashtsble : &lt;b&gt;Hashtable&amp;lt;Integer, String&amp;gt; table = new Hashtable&amp;lt;&amp;gt;()&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Internally Java creates Bucket array&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;6&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;7&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;8&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;9&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;11&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2030" y="1100" width="500" height="220" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-31" value="Initially all buckets are empty" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2125" y="1260" width="210" height="30" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-32" value="Insert first entry : table.put(101, &quot;John&quot;);&lt;div&gt;Now hascode decides which bucket should store101&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Hashtable asks the key : 101.hashcode()&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;-&amp;gt; hascode = 101&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;HAshtable calculates bucket = hash % bucketcount.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;So 101 % 11&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Result = 2&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Store in bucket 2&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;1&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;2&amp;nbsp; -&amp;gt; (101, John)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;3&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Hashtable creates an object internally somethibg like&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Entry{&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;hash=101,&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;key=101,&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;value=&quot;John&quot;,&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;next=null&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;}&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2030" y="1330" width="530" height="250" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-33" value="Now how get() works?&lt;div&gt;table.get(101);&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Hashtable repeats the same process&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Calculates hashcode&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; i.e 101.hashcode()&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Result =101&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Calculate bucket&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;i.e. 101 % 11&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Result =2&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Directly go to bucket 2&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Check key&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;i.e. 101.equals(101);&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Result = true Returns John&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2030" y="1591.77" width="390" height="108.23" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-34" value="The concept of Rehashing, Collision, equals() hascode() contract are similar as HashMap structure explain above" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2040" y="1710" width="350" height="30" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-35" value="" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2560" y="1077.5" width="400" height="132.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-36" value="&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Capacity = 11&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Load factor = 0.75&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Hashtable internally uses array of buckets (Node[])&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Insertion order is not preserved based on hashcode of keys&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Duplicate keys are not allowed but values can be duplicate&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Heterogeneous/Homogeneous object are allowed&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Null is not allowed for key and values.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2550" y="1087.5" width="400" height="100" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-40" value="" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2560" y="1222.5" width="370" height="107.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-41" value="Constructors :&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Hashtable table&amp;nbsp; = new Hashtable&amp;nbsp;();&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Hashtable&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;table&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;= new Hashtable&amp;nbsp;(int initialCapacity);&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Hashtable&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;table&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;= new Hashtable&amp;nbsp;(int initialCapacity, float fillRatio);&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Hashtable&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;table&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;= new Hashtable&amp;nbsp;(Map m);&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2571.25" y="1241.25" width="358.75" height="70" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7cwuXuHkIYcl7uzs2y8c-42" value="New capacity = (11*2) + 1 =23&lt;div&gt;It becomes 11 -&amp;gt; 23 -&amp;gt; 47 -&amp;gt; 95 -&amp;gt; 191 -&amp;gt; 383&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2020" y="1770" width="270" height="30" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
