        <mxCell id="-TBS4qTc4NiXvZP-rJ_w-3" value="HashSet" style="text;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="4520" y="-635" width="70" height="15" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="-TBS4qTc4NiXvZP-rJ_w-4" value="HashSet internally uses HashMap.&lt;div&gt;When you write : &lt;b&gt;HashSet &amp;lt;String&amp;gt; set = new HashSet&amp;lt;&amp;gt;();&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Internally :&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;JetBrains Mono&amp;quot;, monospace; font-size: 9.8pt; background-color: rgb(30, 31, 34); color: rgb(207, 142, 109);&quot;&gt;transient &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;JetBrains Mono&amp;quot;, monospace; font-size: 9.8pt; background-color: rgb(30, 31, 34); color: rgb(188, 190, 196);&quot;&gt;HashMap&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;JetBrains Mono&amp;quot;, monospace; font-size: 9.8pt; background-color: rgb(30, 31, 34); color: rgb(22, 186, 172);&quot;&gt;E&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;JetBrains Mono&amp;quot;, monospace; font-size: 9.8pt; background-color: rgb(30, 31, 34); color: rgb(188, 190, 196);&quot;&gt;,Object&amp;gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;JetBrains Mono&amp;quot;, monospace; font-size: 9.8pt; background-color: rgb(30, 31, 34); color: rgb(199, 125, 187);&quot;&gt;map&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;JetBrains Mono&amp;quot;, monospace; font-size: 9.8pt; background-color: rgb(30, 31, 34); color: rgb(188, 190, 196);&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="4520" y="-607.5" width="330" height="55" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="-TBS4qTc4NiXvZP-rJ_w-5" value="HashSet creates a HashMap.&lt;div&gt;Something like&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;HashMap&amp;lt;String,Object&amp;gt; map =&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;new HashMap&amp;lt;&amp;gt;();&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;HashSet only stores Value but Hasmap needs key and value&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;To solve this Java creates a dummy object : -&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;private static final Object PRESENT =&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;new Object();&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Think&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;PRESENT = &quot;DUMMY&quot; Not actual code.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;When we add:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;set.add(&quot;Java&quot;);&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Internally HashSet does &lt;b&gt;map.put(&quot;Java&quot;, PRESENT);&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;set.add(&quot;Python&quot;);&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Internally HashSet does&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;map.put(&quot;Python&quot;, PRESENT);&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Key&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Value&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Java&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; PRESENT&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Python&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; PRESENT&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="4510" y="-542.5" width="600" height="238.75" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="-TBS4qTc4NiXvZP-rJ_w-7" value="&lt;u&gt;Why use internally HashMap?&lt;/u&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p data-end=&quot;1677&quot; data-start=&quot;1640&quot;&gt;Because HashMap already knows how to:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul data-end=&quot;1755&quot; data-start=&quot;1679&quot;&gt;&lt;li data-end=&quot;1693&quot; data-start=&quot;1679&quot; data-section-id=&quot;w1pknk&quot;&gt;Find buckets&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-end=&quot;1713&quot; data-start=&quot;1694&quot; data-section-id=&quot;phntfz&quot;&gt;Handle collisions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-end=&quot;1730&quot; data-start=&quot;1714&quot; data-section-id=&quot;1a5bdti&quot;&gt;Search quickly&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-end=&quot;1755&quot; data-start=&quot;1731&quot; data-section-id=&quot;f7cvg5&quot;&gt;Prevent duplicate key&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p data-end=&quot;1792&quot; data-start=&quot;1757&quot;&gt;HashSet simply uses those features.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="4510" y="-292.5" width="500" height="140" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="-TBS4qTc4NiXvZP-rJ_w-8" value="HashMap calls &lt;b&gt;&quot;Java&quot;.hashcode()&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt; Suppose 2301506&lt;div&gt;HashMap calculates bucket&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Suppose bucket = 5&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Bucket empty ? No. Store node :&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Bucket 5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; (Java,PRESENT)&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="4510" y="-152.5" width="330" height="70" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="-TBS4qTc4NiXvZP-rJ_w-9" value="&lt;u&gt;How duplication detection works?&lt;/u&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Now if we write again &lt;b&gt;set.add(&quot;Java&quot;);&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Intenally it calls &lt;b&gt;map.put(&quot;Java&quot;, PRESENT)&lt;/b&gt;;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;HashMAp goes to same bucket.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;FInd existing key :&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;storedKey.equals(&quot;Java&quot;);&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;Returns&amp;nbsp; = true&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Meaning key already exists. HashMap refuses insertion therefore HashSet also refuses it. HashSet oes not have its own duplicate logic . It depends on HashMap&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="4510" y="-82.5" width="390" height="110" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="-TBS4qTc4NiXvZP-rJ_w-10" value="" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="5060" y="-620" width="400" height="127.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="-TBS4qTc4NiXvZP-rJ_w-11" value="&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Capacity = 16&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Load factor = 0.75&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Underline data structure - HashMap&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Insertion order is not preserved based on hashcode of keys&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Duplicate objects are not allowed&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Heterogeneous/Homogeneous object are allowed&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Null is allowed only once.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="5050" y="-610" width="400" height="100" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="-TBS4qTc4NiXvZP-rJ_w-12" value="" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="5060" y="-476.87" width="360" height="107.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="-TBS4qTc4NiXvZP-rJ_w-13" value="Constructors :&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;HashSet s&amp;nbsp; = new HashSet&amp;nbsp;();&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;HashSet&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;s&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;= new HashSet&amp;nbsp;(int initialCapacity);&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;HashSet&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;s&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;= new HashSet&amp;nbsp;(int initialCapacity, float fillRatio);&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;HashSet&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;s&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;= new HashSet&amp;nbsp;(Collection c);&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
